# Boolean Logic

## Definition
Boolean Logic is a mathematical system used in digital electronics that works with only two values:
- 0 (Logic LOW / False)
- 1 (Logic HIGH / True)

It is the foundation of digital circuits and Verilog design.

## Boolean Variables
Boolean variables can have only one of two values:
- 0
- 1

Example:
A = 0
B = 1

## Boolean Expressions

AND:
Y = A & B

OR:
Y = A | B

NOT:
Y = ~A

NAND:
Y = ~(A & B)

NOR:
Y = ~(A | B)

XOR:
Y = A ^ B

XNOR:
Y = ~(A ^ B)

## Truth Tables
A truth table shows all possible input combinations and their outputs.

